<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100012559891316></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100012559891316><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100012559891316>RE: Newbie questions</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100012559891316#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=79214><span id=Scholar>Ravensveil</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>242 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 10th 8:39 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.13]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is a bracelet you can buy from 'chanters for dex. Onyx I think. should sell to you for around 3-5 plat depending on what kind of demand they are getting. There are a couple of rings you can get for about that price. Bearing in mind, these are silver. Other metals will get more costly. Enchanted jewelry isn't cheap to make. <br>it's got to be enchanter, or it won't give you bonuses. <br><br>If you are really interested in obtaining enchanted jewelry on a reg basis, and being able to upgrade it regularly, I would suggest training in the jewelry skill. It taint cheap, but it can be worth it. You can have an enchanter enchant your metal for you. It will usually cost you, but you might can also work out a trade depending on what you have found or what you are making. Not all 'chanters take up jewel craft, but will gladly make a couple of plat enchanting metals for you. The advantage here is that you can buy metals as you can afford them, any of them, and find chanters of the appropriate level to trade/buy the enchantment from. So, you'll be making platinum jewelry at any level (which will sell for far more than it will cost you to make/have enchanted). <br><br>I know that there is some armor that will raise wis. Just saw wristbands last night that I would love to have...<br><br>My 2cp to add.<br><br>Bruce lee?<br>&nbsp;<br>"In waking a tiger, use a very long stick." -Mao Tse-Tung. Did he go to Stonebrunt too?</td></tr>
