<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99910935912829></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99910935912829><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99910935912829>Level 27-30</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99910935912829#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85932><span id= >batmaniac</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 29th 2:22 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Little tip for any bards at level 27-30.  Charm kiting in the Karanas will help you get TO and THROUGH hell level in no time.  Here's how to do it -<br><br>Find 2 (yes, TWO) black or yellow cons (Choon and Froon work well at 28-29, and gnolls by the spires in SK are good at 27).  Charm one and stick it on the other.  Immediatly start singing selo's (with drum).  RE-SELECT the SAME mob you charmed first.  When charm breaks, run backwards with selo's in circles.  Re-charm the SAME mob.  Stick him on his buddy again.  Repeat.  Eventually your pet should kill the other one, if only because he's getting the first hit every time they fight.  By the end of it all, you should have one dead and one close... then just kite the last one with selo's and Brusco's Boastful Bellow till he starts to run, then melee till dead... vwala.<br><br>I used this tactic to solo Choon AND Froon in WKarana, and there were level 32 characters who thought I was a god because of it... great exp and if you don't screw it up, you should never even get hit.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
